  <section class="city-intro">
    <div class="city-intro-inner">
      <div class="city-intro-content">
        <h2>Appliance Repair in Tustin — New Development and Old Town, Both Covered</h2>
        <p>Tustin is a city of contrasts. Tustin Legacy — built on the former Marine Corps Air Station — is one of the larger new-urbanist developments in OC, with thousands of homes in the 5-10 year age range and appliances to match. Old Town Tustin has craftsman bungalows, Spanish Colonial homes, and housing stock that goes back to the 1920s. North Tustin trends toward larger, established homes with higher-end kitchen installations.</p>
        <p>Our technicians know all three. In Tustin Legacy we see Samsung flex drawer failures, LG drain pump filter clogs, and GE sensor issues on the first generation of appliances now hitting their 5-8 year service life. In Old Town we see older appliances at repair-or-replace crossroads. In Tustin Ranch and North Tustin we see KitchenAid and Sub-Zero calls that require the right OEM parts.</p>
        <p>We're part of our regular Orange County routes from Irvine. Diagnostic fee is $89, credited toward the repair. Call <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="city-sidebar">
