        <h2>Tustin Legacy — What 5-8 Year Appliances Actually Need</h2>
        <p>Tustin Legacy is now at the age where its first generation of appliances are hitting characteristic failure points. Samsung and LG refrigerators installed in 2017-2020 are showing ice maker wire harness failures, linear compressor early wear, and flex drawer control board failures. These are known failure patterns for these models at this age — not defects, just wear curves.</p>
        <p>LG front-load washers at the 4-6 year mark frequently develop drain pump filter clogs — the filter needs quarterly cleaning, but most homeowners don't know it exists until an OE error appears and water sits in the drum. We show every Tustin Legacy LG washer owner where the filter is before we leave.</p>
        <p>GE ranges in the Legacy have started showing oven sensor failures, particularly after self-clean cycles which put the sensor under thermal stress. F2 error after a self-clean is almost always the sensor — a $50-80 OEM part and 90 minutes of labor, not the control board replacement some companies quote.</p>
        <p>Old Town and the historic neighborhoods are a different story — appliances there can be anything from 5 to 20+ years old. We assess each one honestly and give you a repair-or-replace recommendation before starting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

